# Git Commit Message Template
# 
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <type>: Specifies the nature of the change. Common types include:
#   feat     - A new feature
#   fix      - A bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation changes
#   style    - Code style changes (formatting, missing semi-colons, etc.)
#   refactor - Code refactoring without changing functionality
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Routine tasks or maintenance
#
# <scope>: (Optional) The section of the codebase affected, such as `parser`, `UI`, or `database`.
# <subject>: A short summary of the change (50 characters max).
#
# Body: (Optional) A more detailed explanation, wrapped at 72 characters per line.
# Footer: (Optional) For referencing issues, breaking changes, or other notes.
#
# Example:
# feat(parser): enhance syntax analysis for edge cases
#
# Improved the parser to handle previously unrecognized syntax patterns,
# ensuring accurate analysis of complex code structures.
#
# Closes #456
